# Cursor / Windsurf Rules — YitPush (yp)

## Project Overview

`yp` (YitPush) is a .NET 10 global CLI tool for AI-powered Git commits and Azure DevOps management. It supports multiple AI providers: OpenAI, Anthropic, Google Gemini, DeepSeek, and OpenRouter.

## Architecture

The codebase uses a single `partial class Program` split across multiple files by feature:

```
Program.cs              — Main(), ShowHelp(), CheckForUpdates(), all constants
Models.cs               — Data model classes (outside Program class)
Commands/
  CommitCommand.cs      — yp commit logic
  PrCommand.cs          — yp pr logic
  SetupCommand.cs       — yp setup + alias installer
  CheckoutCommand.cs    — yp checkout logic
Providers/
  AiProviders.cs        — ConfigManager + HTTP calls for all AI providers
Git/
  GitHelpers.cs         — All git process operations
AzureDevOps/
  AzureDevOpsCommand.cs — Routing + interactive menu + help
  AzureDevOpsHelpers.cs — All Azure REST API calls and work item logic
```

## Coding Conventions

- All methods are `private static` inside `partial class Program`
- Use `AnsiConsole` (Spectre.Console) for all user-facing output — never raw `Console.Write` for messages
- Use `AnsiConsole.Prompt` / `SelectionPrompt` for interactive menus
- Always include a `← Back` (`BackOption` constant) option in selection menus
- Prefer `async/await` throughout — no blocking `.Result` or `.Wait()`
- Git operations go in `Git/GitHelpers.cs`, use `RunGitOutput()` for simple stdout reads
- AI API calls go in `Providers/AiProviders.cs`
- Azure DevOps REST calls go in `AzureDevOps/AzureDevOpsHelpers.cs`

## Constants (defined in Program.cs)

```csharp
ApiMaxTokens = 8000
ApiTimeoutSeconds = 120
ApiMaxContextTokens = 131072
AzFieldEffortHH = "Custom.EsfuerzoEstimadoHH"
AzFieldEffortRealHH = "Custom.EsfuerzoRealHH"
AzFieldRemainingWork = "Microsoft.VSTS.Scheduling.RemainingWork"
```

Always use these constants — never hardcode the values.

## AI Provider Pattern

To add a new AI provider:
1. Add its base URL to `GetDefaultBaseUrl()` in `AiProviders.cs`
2. Add its model list to `GetDefaultModelsForProvider()` in `SetupCommand.cs`
3. If it uses OpenAI-compatible API: route to `CallOpenAiCompatibleApi()` in `CallAiApi()`
4. If it has a unique API format: add `Call<Name>Api()` and add a case in `CallAiApi()`

## Error Handling

- API calls use a 3-attempt retry with exponential backoff (1s, 2s, 4s)
- Use `catch { /* Silent */ }` only for truly non-critical background tasks (e.g., `CheckForUpdates`)
- Show user-friendly errors with `AnsiConsole.MarkupLine("[red]❌ ...[/]")`

## Config

- User config: `~/.yitpush/config.json` (managed by `ConfigManager` in `AiProviders.cs`)
- Version check cache: `~/.yitpush/version-check.json`
- Env vars (`OPENAI_API_KEY`, `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY`, etc.) override stored config keys

## Do Not

- Do not add new top-level files for single methods — put them in the appropriate existing file
- Do not change method visibility from `private static` without a strong reason
- Do not use `Console.WriteLine` for user messages — use `AnsiConsole.MarkupLine`
- Do not hardcode Azure DevOps field names — use `AzField*` constants
- Do not create new model classes inside `partial class Program` — add them to `Models.cs`
